physical_examinations.relevant_findings: General: Alert & oriented, no acute distress; HEENT: No scleral icterus, mucous membranes moist; Cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs/gallops/rubs; Pulmonary: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no wheezes/rales/ronchi; Abdomen: Soft, nondistended, nontender, no rebound or guarding, normoactive bowel sounds, subcostal incision clean/dry/intact with staples; Extremities: No edema, warm and well perfused
